<item>
            <title>[LU-7977] Change MB/s to MiB/s in lnet_selftest reporting</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7977</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;According to the standards of data rate units (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Data_rate_units&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Data_rate_units&lt;/a&gt;), an MB is 1,000,000 whereas an MiB is 1,048,576.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When calculating bandwidth in lnet_selftest, we are dividing by 1,048,576 to get the MiB/s but reporting it as MB/s.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This ticket is to fix the reported units to be MiB/s for accuracy.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
